### Get Assessment values                   [POST /user-info/get-assessment-values]

Return the assessment values calculated for the user after an assessment session. 

This method could be used to show to a user his cognitive historical but it is not build for batch downloading actions.

The session_id parameter must be an assessment session.

**Assessment indicators**: There are three different indicators data types. They would help to understand the assessmentIndicators values.<br/>

WELLNESS: This indicator is placing the user values into poor or optimal wellness ranges.
    
```json
{
    "interpretation": {
        "dataType": "WELLNESS",
        "description": {
            "POOR_WELLNESS_RANGE": [
                0,
                "minRange"
            ],
            "OPTIMAL_WELLNESS_RANGE": [
                "medRange",
                "maxRange"
            ]
        }
    },
    "values": [...]
}
```
        
FLIPPED_RISK: This indicator is placing the user values into high or optimal risk ranges.

```json
{
    "interpretation": {
        "dataType": "FLIPPED_RISK",
        "description": {
            "HIGH_RISK_RANGE": [
                0,
                "minRange"
            ],
            "OPTIMAL_RISK_RANGE": [
                "medRange",
                "maxRange"
            ]
        }
    },
    "values": [...]
}
```

RISK: This indicator is placing the user values into no dectectable risk or high risk ranges.
   
```json
{
    "interpretation": {
        "dataType": "RISK",
        "description": {
            "NO_DETECTABLE_RISK_RANGE": [
                0,
                "minRange"
            ],
            "HIGH_RISK_RANGE": [
